comment: I didn’t actually send this yet because it’s hard as nails, but wanted to leave a comment in support of Andy’s take. I’m an intermediate climber, climbing for years, and comfortably climbing v3/4 and projecting v5s pre-lockdown. I’m back to March-level strength, but the joy of climbing a nice route at my limit is becoming quite rare here. I warm up through V2 and never struggle with those, the hop on my v3/4 projects that feel impossible for the rest of the session. It’s left me a little confused on how to even spend my time at the gym—there’s so little outside of my warmups that I can repeat that I have to project every session, which can be confidence crushing. Would really appreciate seeing more variety in difficulty in this range.
harder than expected for a v1
I enjoyed this one, it’s interesting for a v2.
challenging finish, in a good way. was fun to work out the right place for my feet to top it
fun climb, really liked the finish!
I loved the kneebar finish. that said, kneebar finish for a V1? saw a lot of confused newer climbers on this
I’m on the weaker side, but the big move at the top feels hard for a v1. since I can’t lock off, I had to do a kneebar. I liked the climb, just feel it’s not a v1
